title: Life Science HiSET.3.2
prompt: The "notable finding" mentioned in the last paragraph suggests that
feedback: The correct answer is "Frog tissue retains pesticides, even though they are not detectable in water or soil." The scientist says that there were pesticides detected in frog tissues but not in water samples and suggests that frog tissues are a more reliable indicator of pesticides. Because the scientist believes frog tissues are a reliable indicator, the implication isn’t that the frogs migrated from elsewhere. The implication is that frog tissue retains pesticides, when water or soil may not. That’s what would make it a more accurate indicator.
